<item>
            <title>[LU-11732] stats collection script</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11732</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;in DDN-554 we need quite amount of data to analyse performance degradation. this isn&apos;t the only case we such a data is needed. every time we ask customer to collect this data, explain how to do so, etc.&lt;br/&gt;
it makes sense to have a script doing this.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;ideally it should be a single command spawning all (or specified) servers.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;yes another useful feature would be to show some data online, so that user could watch how servers are doing in different areas. for example, read/write rates for every OSS/OST - then user can easily identify underperforming target. similar mode can be used to monitor other stats (IO sizes, IO times, avg.seek, etc).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
